title: Back From The Dead
body:
Pairing: Sam x Reader

Word Count: 429

“Nathan!” You giggled as your now boyfriend, Nathan, tickled your sides.

About a year ago, your fiancé, Sam, done a nose dive into the depths of hell to save all of mankind. How you were going to move on? You had no clue. You kept Sam close to your heart, meaning you put the ring he gave you on a plain, silver chain. Nathan didn’t seem to mind- he’s also didn’t know what you and Sam had been through together.

“Nathan, please! Stop!” You cried in laughter. “No, honestly, I need to cook supper!”

You hadn’t seen Dean since Sam died. Nor had you see Bobby. Or Cas really. You missed them. All of them. But now, you had a life with Nathan. And although you wanted a family with Sam, you now had one with Nate.

“And what dish will it be tonight, babe?” He pressed a slow kiss against your lips.

“Spaghetti and garlic bread?”

A day later, you were out and about your new neighborhood, when the most expected thing in the entire universe happened. A monster. Vampire to be exact. You should’ve put the pieces together before now! You had a bad feeling about that night, your hunter instincts were tingling. You wished you had convinced Nathan to stay home. But he was headstrong. The vamp got the drop on you, almost sinking his fangs into your neck. You reacted quickly however. You were a bit rusty, but not rusty enough that you couldn’t handle one, pitiful vampire. But then more came. You were getting overpowered.

“Y/N!” Nathan cried out.

Your view of Nathan had been cut off when a vamp stepped out in front of you. He charged at you. You shielded your face with your arms and squeezed your eyes shut, expecting it to be your last moment. But when you heard the clean, brisk slice of a blade, you opened your eyes to find…

“SAM!” You cried out, running into his arms.

He wrapped his arms around you tightly.

“Y/N!” He said softly.

You pulled away quickly, your hands gripping onto his arms, “wait, how?”

“I-I don’t know.” Sam shrugged.

“Is it really you?” You choked, letting a tear roll down your cheek.

He did the tests in front of you. Your mind totally absent, you pulled Sam down into you and kissed him hard and quick at first, but then eased it into a soft and slow one. From behind Sam, you heard someone clearing their throat.

Then a low, gruff voice sang out, “um… hello?! What about me!”

summary:
Crowley knew it was decadent, to order a slice of cake when he would eat only a bite or
two, but if Aziraphale would finish it,...
body:
Crowley knew it was decadent, to order a slice of cake when he would eat only a bite or two, but if Aziraphale would finish it, what was the harm? And no, perhaps Aziraphale wouldn’t usually order a rabbit stew, or a lobster thermidor, would order something cheaper, more modest, but if Crowley egged him on, begged him to order it, so that he could have a taste—

Aziraphale would.

And the pleasure of eating himself, Crowley didn’t think, the pleasure of tasting the several dishes the two of them usually spread between them in the course of a meal, was nothing compared to the pleasure of seeing Aziraphale eat.

He remembered the first time he’d tempted the angel into eating. They’d eaten a meal together, he remembered, the both of them sitting in some luxuriant house on the edge of a verdant forest, and he said if Aziraphale would let him tempt him with gluttony, he would listen to any moralistic lecture Aziraphale wanted to give him, and Aziraphale had talked and talked and talked, and between words, he would let Crowley press morsels of meat and cheese and sweet paste and fruit into his mouth, and such noises as he’d made, soft moans of pleasure at the taste, the way he chewed so delicately, the way he swallowed—

He’d made Crowley eat, too. He’d fed him a bite for every bite Crowley had fed him, not realising that Crowley lacked his appetite until Crowley had awkwardly – politely – told him so. He’d been so embarrassed, and Crowley had felt sleepy, giving into his serpentine instincts and sprawling in Aziraphale’s lap, bundled in the skirt of his handsome robes, as a snake.

As he’d dropped hazily into sleep, he’d been aware of Aziraphale still eating, finishing the rest of the plate they’d been sharing, and he’d felt warm and comfortable in his place, liquid scale in his lap.

god i love writing these two and food

summary: aziraphale and crowley spending a whole day together in some picturesque little town that looks like it’s been plucked from a...
body: aziraphale and crowley spending a whole day together in some picturesque little town that looks like it’s been plucked from a hallmark card. feeding the swans. sipping wine on the patio of a family owned restaurant. spending time out on the lake in some boat fit for two, the alps as their backdrop. aziraphale reads from a book he’s brought along, while crowley naps in the warm, summer sun. and later, when they kiss, the taste of sachertorte, a chocolate cake they’d shared for dinner, is still on aziraphale’s lips.

Isn't

body:
Why Crowley is so relatable:

  • Would like to be considered cool
  • Isn’t
  • Is actually a complete dork
  • Thinks black clothes and sunglasses will make the trick
  • They actually don’t
  • Is stuck listening to Queen songs on repeat
  • Useless gay
  • Will sleep for a century if given the chance
  • Remembers things when they’re no longer relevant (“DUCK!”)
  • Everything he does screws him over in the end
  • Priorities: music and sushi

summary: Hi! Could I please request a Supernatural ship? (If you're still doing these!) I'm a bi female from Ireland. I'm short, I have...
question: Hi! Could I please request a Supernatural ship? (If you're still doing these!) I'm a bi female from Ireland. I'm short, I have curly brown hair and blue eyes. I love to watch Netflix, make edits and write. I'm shy and work hard at school :)
answer:
I ship you with Crowley. He would love your Irish accent and how short you are. To him you are extremely adorable and he would tug at your curls teasingly. He would enjoy chilling and watching Netflix with you. While you’re in school or working on an edit he would go and do his own work running He’ll.

Small Scene

It had been a long day at school and all you wanted to do was go home and relax. College definitely wasn’t easy to handle. You walked through the front door and kicked your shoes off hanging your bag up as you did so.

“Hello darling.”

A smile lit up your face as you lifted your head and spotted Crowley. He stood in the middle of the living room look sharp as always and sporting his cocky smirk.

“I wasn’t expecting you. What are you doing here?” You ask as you make your way toward him. He takes you by the arms and kisses you breathless.

“First I wanted to do that seeing as I’m the only one who can. And second I thought we could watch one of your shows together after your long day. I’ll take your mind of it darling as long as you take mine off if dealing with those plaid wearing morons and the idiotic demons.”

“You’ve got a deal,” you teased. His smirk depended and he kissed you again.

“Now it’s sealed. You’re mine forever.”

title: Blog update
body:
Some really nice art in the #good omens tag lately, I’m loving it. Queue is full and running happily- anyone want me to bump it up to 3 posts per day?

  • Tags have been updated to include #ineffable husbands
  • Ask box is now open, (I doodle sometimes, feel free to send in requests, results not guaranteed- also if you want racy things you gotta ask off anon.)

Things I’ve been looking for: anyone have a twitter or some other place they post racy GO art? I desire all the lemons.

by blueberryspacekitten

In the early autumn of 1973, a young jazz singer, Castiel, sets of to the city to earn fame, money and living. In a small bar near the outskirts of the city, rarely do any customers visit, but Cas loves to sing nonetheless. His beautiful whisky-like voice intoxicates almost everyone and he already has the women fawning, some men too, dare he say.

But what seems to be a harmless pleasure filled night with one green eyed, soft voiced vagabond, soon turns out to be a bigger web of mysteries, and in the middle of it, Dean Winchester.

Who is this man and why is he even here? Why is he carrying a huge wad of cash? And what about the blood on his black gloves and boots? Is he really as innocent as he looks? And what’s with his his weird obsession with Castiel?

Looking for answers, Castiel wanders way deeper than he should have, and now he doesn’t know how to escape.

blog.name: ygrain-synaerasis
blog.title: L'Echappée Belle d' Ygraïn
blog.description:
" Elle voulait une vie d'aventures, une vie folle, une vie plus grande qu'elle.Et l'on disait tout autour d'elle : [Ygraïn] rêve". Timothée de Fombelle, Victoria rêve

Je ne sais pas dessiner, les artworks que vous verrez ici ne sont pas les miens. Mais vous trouverez toujours un lien vers une gallerie de leurs auteurs. Personnellement, je ne fais que des montages (wallpaper, digiscrap, bannière ...) à partir de captures d'écran (screencap).. Ce tumblr est ma gallerie de rêves éphémères, mon échappée belle où je viens me ressourcer, me changer les idées, trouver un support à mes rêveries grâce aux fabuleux arts de d'autres artistes. .
Pour me contacter, en cas de problème: ygrain@gmail.com

Sinon: mon blog de lecture est: https://les-lectures-d-ygrain.tumblr.com/
